external_knowledge:
- A 'senior checkout' refers to a checkout by a senior citizen, implying that the person checking out the item is above a certain age (typically 60 or 65 years old, but the exact age may vary depending on the library's definition); 
- The 'total checkouts' include all checkouts, regardless of the patron's age; 
- 'Item sub-type' categorizes items into genres or categories like Fiction, Non-Fiction, or Biography.
